HEADWORD: Censual
<hw>Cen"su*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>censualis</ets>, fr. <ets>census</ets>.]</ety> <def>Relating to, or
containing, a census.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He caused the whole realm to be described in a <qex>censual</qex>
roll.</q> <rj><qau>Sir R. Baker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Censurable</ent>⟦br⟧
